	<p>It really isnt a big deal. <br />
<br />
I mean it isnt going to cure cancer or anything.<br />
<br />
But for my gaming doller. WoW is superior to EQ in fun, polish, support, and most importantly mindset. <br />
<br />
EQ was a great game when it started. But the years and shoddy management have run it down considerbly. Now. to a new player that wants to get into a MMORG EQ is not the direction I would steer anyone. Wow is. But. If they wanted to raid large scale targets with a virtual horde of players. EQ still wins hands down.<br />
<br />
EQ has the most content. 6 years sees to that. But much of it is conflicting, and Obsolete.  I mean Paladuel caverns for xp and bazzar for gear. Most new players will never know east karanas Like I do. Or west karanas. They will never learn of Pyzjin. Or even glimpse Tovax Vmar. <br />
<br />
EQ has been changed from a RPG to a tactical simulator. And to most players "the real game starts at 65-70"<br />
<br />
In WoW, "<b>The real game starts at level 1"</b> <br />
<br />
That is the differance.<br />
<br />
Snoww Silverhammer Bashy RABID bear E marr (Retired)<br />
<br />
Wandering the War torn lands of Azeroth as Feather Earthen Ring server.</p>
	
	
	
	
	
