	<p>Chances are good that WoW will go the same route and in 5 years be a completely different game, but it is not that way NOW.<br />
<br />
What it is NOW is simply FUN; EQ is not fun NOW. Remember that feeling waaaay back when you couldn't wait to get home to finish that quest? Remember the first time you traversed the Karanas and went.....holy s++t this is awesome. It's the feeling that makes you come back to a game over and over until the feeling is gone. Atleast for me, that feeling was gone from EQ and I have found it again in WoW.<br />
<br />
In WoW, tradeskills are actually fun and <b>useful</b> from the very beginning. As a Tauren Shaman I have made every piece of armor I am wearing with my Skinning and Leatherworking skills. It's a whole new world to explore and to reiterate from the beginning of this post, <b>IT"S FUN!</b></p>
	
	
	
