<tr>
	<td class="alt2" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>Vazzkorr</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Initiate<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Aug 2002<br />
	
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>Anyone that thinks that WoW will be like EQ is now 5 years from now hasnt played the game.<br />
<br />
Face it, right now, EQ really starts at lvl 65...and soon that will be lvl 70...<br />
<br />
Why?  Bad planning, bad design and lack of well planned limitations.<br />
<br />
The result was excessive twinkage, and because of the incredible grinding (read non-fun) required to level a lot of power leveling.<br />
<br />
A lot of people ended up multi-boxing just to get anything done.<br />
<br />
Sure, later SoE finally started putting in some level limits on gear and added all the incredibly stupid flagging to limit access to new gear, but it was just badly done.  The result was the effective closing off of huge areas of the game to anyone that disliked raiding or didnt want to be guilded.<br />
<br />
WoW does it differently.  You almost never feel like your grinding, at least so far...the twinking that can be done is minor and just really not required.<br />
<br />
Gear you get from mobs you kill is useable (wow what a concept, that early on in the game you can actually improve your character without having to buy stuff that other players looted)<br />
<br />
Tradeskills are worthwhile and actually dont lead to carpal-tunnel...and you can actually use some of what your making...<br />
<br />
Does WoW have the content depth of EQ, no, of course not, but the viable existing content already in someways exceeds EQ, because its all new and all worth doing at present.<br />
<br />
Huge areas of EQ are now just wasted space...quests were almost totally useless in EQ except for a few and even those were really never designed properly.  Anytime a guild/multi-group force is required to finish a quest, well, what can I say...imposed limits.<br />
<br />
Currently as I havent seen the end-game in WoW, I cant really comment on longevity, but I can comment on the fun-factor, and frankly there is no comparison..its WoW hands down...<br />
<br />
After having spend over 5 years in the world of EQ, I frankly see nothing pulling me back.<br />
<br />
Vazzkorr</p>
	
	
	
	
	
