<tr>
	<td class="alt2" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>niwggib</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Disciple<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Dec 2003<br />
	Location: Innoruuk
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>I am not sure I know exactly what it is.<br />
<br />
It just seems less tedious. There is so many things to do. You can actually get a nice drop from yard_trash_mob_1850. The quest are nice. Some require just ordinary drops that mobs normally drop. Others require special drops and they do not drop until you are on the actual quest.<br />
<br />
If you need a "Boss Mob" for a quest and you share that quest with you group. Every single person in your group that loots the mob gets the quest item.<br />
<br />
There is no kill stealing. If you damage it first, it is your mob. It does not matter if you only do one point of damage and someone else kills the other 500hps when the mob dies you get exp (lessened to some extent) and you get to go loot the mob.<br />
<br />
Travel - you have to go to places first and talk to griphon(sp) trainers and once you do certain trainers can fly to certain cities. The rides are amazing. You can see stuff going on as you fly over the world seems seamless. I have run into 3 zones so far. Travel between the two continents and there is a train between Ironforge and Stormwind you have to zone into the "station" on either end. You can however after you travel to the last two fly there with out having to zone.<br />
<br />
That might seem like a bad thing but you can usually outrun aggro on mobs. Lets say you tag one mob. He is yours and no one else can steal him from you. So all the sudden another mob decides to jump in and you cannot handle the two of them. If you start running the mobs will only chase you so far. Once you out distance them the mob that you previously aggro'd will run back to his spawn point and become a free mob again. <br />
<br />
Lets say that someone tried to help you and you just got out of range as the mobs lost aggro. You will not be able to hit the mob until he gets back to their spawn point. They will ignore you and they will evade or resist any attack until they are back at their spawn point. Then if you followed them back into their aggro radius they will attack you or you can attack them. This for the most part eliminates training.<br />
<br />
Tradeskills are fun. They are pretty simple for the most part but fun none the less.<br />
<br />
Dying - Who cares! I mean seriously you spend a few silver to repair your armor and the time it takes to get back to your body. <br />
<br />
It is a simple game but I have way more fun than I did in EQ. This comes from a long time EQ addict too. My 7 year old now has a few characters and begs me to play with him all the time now. (Blackmail for homework ROCKS!!!!) But now my 4 year old is eyeing the computer and wanting to play too. He can finish all most all of the levels for Jedi Knight, which is their favorite multiplayer games!</p>
	
	
	
		<div>__________________<br />Niwggib<br />
_________</div>
	
	
