	<!-- message -->
	<p><blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />Originally Posted by <b>RedChief</b><br /><i>WoW to me has been overly simplistic.  The risk to dying is not there.  The rewards for grouping dont seem to be there.</i><hr size="1" /></blockquote>There are plenty of risks to dying, for I have died many times.  I admit, the risk of dying is fairly low for lower level characters (pre 20) tho.  <br />
<br />
Corpse retrieval in general is much less stressful than it is in EQ.  There are times that I have died getting my corpse.  (Died deep in a cave and it had respawned by the time I got back, leading to a another death).<br />
<br />
<br />
The rewards for grouping are there.  You will not see it until your upper teens and up when elite quests and instanced zones are made available to you.<br />
<br />
<br />
The game itself is fun and has removed just about everything bad that was in EQ.  Quests are actually fun to do and have meaning.  You are never forced to camp trivial green con mobs for hours on end.  You are not forced to sit in a zone to forage a rare drop to obtain a component.</p>
	
	
	
