	<p><blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />Originally Posted by <b>Jenguran</b><br /><i>One big worry I have with WoW and this is one that won't be showing its ugly head for abit is that though Blizzard games are known to be very well done, they also get known to get severly hacked.  Now on a PvE aspect that really doesn't mean much, yea EQ has its hacks out there and I imagine they get used pretty harshly on the Zeks, I wouldn't know since I don't PvP and have no interest in it.<br />
<br />
Problems are PvP is a part of WoW and a packet is in many peoples eyes theirs to do with as they choose.  From those who are currently playing WoW and especially from those who have used cheats in EQ how do you think this will impact the gameplay?</i><hr size="1" /></blockquote>I think Blizzard has learned the hard way to counter hacks, so I wouldnt expect to see the same phenomenon surface in WOW as it did in D2 before they patched it up.<br />
<br />
My experience from having played several years on a PVP server tells me that hacks and ShowEQ like tools have a minimal impact on the game as whole. Sure, there was one or two griefers who would use ShowEQ to track you in the zone, but chances to run into the same persons day after day are very slim. Besides, the benefits gained from ShowEQ can be duplicated by having the track skill (read: Ranger with Trueshot = teh pain).<br />
<br />
However... what REALLY destroys the game is plat/item dupes. It kills the economy and ruins one of the more intriguing aspects of the game. Whereas PVP hackers are so few and do so little impact, its the "peaceful" hacking that is the big killer.<br />
<br />
It is my belief that Blizzard will be able to counter these problems atleast aswell as SOE has done, so unless item/money dupe occurs in WOW, i think we will have little to worry about.</p>
	
	
	
