	<p><blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />WoW to me has been overly simplistic. The risk to dying is not there. The rewards for grouping dont seem to be there.<hr size="1" /></blockquote>Obviously you've never done an instanced dungeon.<br />
I went with a group to Wailing Caverns to do 6 quests I had for the zone.<br />
All of them were Elite quests.<br />
The reward for clearing the zone was a staff with 20 dps, but I didn't end up even needing it because I won a 21.5 dps staff from the end boss of the zone.<br />
In comparison, after 5 full levels of hunting, the current reward for doing yellow quests for me are still only 17dps or less staves.<br />
We also saw a 15dps 1h mace drop off one of the named mobs for the quests.<br />
In comparison, the absolute best weapon I can me with 150+ blacksmithing so far is still only about 12 dps, and same for comparable item drops (I just sold a 12.5 dps mace the other day for nearly a full gold piece).<br />
Grouping to kill the elites is where the big items are...</p>
	
	
	
