	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>Elite mobs are the fix for mobs dying too fast.<br />
Also, fighting mobs 1 or 2 or 3 or even 4 levels above you makes for longer and scarier fights.<br />
I don't know how it'll be at higher levels, but IMO the elite instanced dungeons need for more mobs to be grouped together.<br />
Making a dungeon full of elite mobs, and then making them all solo pull or 2 pull doesn't especially make for a tough dungeon.<br />
Making the pulls come in sets of 3 and 4 and 5 at a time would make for much more interesting fights to deal with with some real risk of death.<br />
The clearing I've done of Wailing Caverns with a few others was pretty damn easy except for the final boss fight.<br />
The challenge of everything needs to be pumped up a weee bit IMO, especially when there's virtually no penalty for dying.</p>
	
	
	
