	<p>for myself, the kicker has been that WoW has done the shaman class right. it's what I thought the eq shaman was going to be 4 years ago, hoped it would be recently, and now realize that it never will be. I don't know what draws me to the shaman class in most games that offer them, but imo WoW offers the best example so far. <br />
<br />
personally, I think that many 'die-hard' eq fans (and I have been one for many years) are protesting a bit much about WoW. who are you really trying to convince that WoW sucks? I think you're trying to convince yourselves for the most part. let it go already, be happy for those of us that have moved on and found something that we enjoy as much as we used to enjoy EQ. both games aren't going anywhere for a while (though open recruitment w/ reduced reqs is way up for even the most uber guilds in EQ these days <img src="images/smilies/smile.gif" border="0" alt="" title="smile" smilieid="1" />) so take the time to try it out and see for yourself. of course, if you go in thinking 'EQ roxorz!! no way WoW can be any good!' your bias is probably going to cloud your opinion anyway. and that's cool too <img src="images/smilies/smile.gif" border="0" alt="" title="smile" smilieid="1" /></p>
	
	
	
