<tr>
	<td class="alt2" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>Litgruv</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Heyokah<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: May 2002<br />
	
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>I think i summed it up best in a post i made in the WoW forum. Do you want to play the game from the people coming up with the ideas or the game from the people stealing ideas from all over and slapping their logo on it.<br />
<br />
When i look at blizzard i see a long time experienced company that has a lore laid out for this game from games prior, they have a real sense of the fantasy adventure and what makes it fun. They listen to the customers much better then SoE and try to not shove things down your throat and make you do it how they say. They know this is a product for us and while they have to govern it and maintain its continuaty, its our interest that is making the game.<br />
<br />
Another thing is camps dont exists, atleast not like in EQ. I was reading a thread the other day about someone camping a mob for 4 hours and not getting a drop they need and will have to come back the next day and invest probably another 4. I remember camping my VP key and camping 1 mob alone for 16 straight, none stop, not leaving my chair. This is not a problem in WoW.<br />
<br />
In WoW goruping is not a must, 1 class is not a required class. If you dont have a priest a shaman or druid or pally or someone that like to bandage alot will do fine. You can actualy solo effectivly without 10 minutes of down time as a warrior or any class.<br />
<br />
PvP is actualy fun. There is a reward and penalty system in place to encourage honorable play int he PvP and its simply a more advanced system with town sieges and 1 on1  PvP.<br />
<br />
WoW is just more fun in my opinion, im not knocking EQ or EQ2, but in my life i find that WoW offers the perfect balance of fun, excitment and the ability to quit any time. There is no real exp penalties for death also. I dont mind paying a durability price, but exp is hard earned and hold you back from progression. Plus its just new and a change, that alone is a huge redeeming factor. For me it was time to move on from EQ. WoW or no WoW.</p>
	
	
	
		<div>__________________<br /><center><b>Its just my opinion, it could be wrong.</b><br />
