<tr>
	<td class="alt1" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>Blazz</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Fateseer<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Sep 2003<br />
	Location: Upstate, NY
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>I would honestly liketo go back, and quote 20 of these posts, and add the words "for now" on the end of every one. <br />
<br />
I havent played WoW, but its obviously a great game. Its a game that is helping both old-time EQ players find that "magic" again and, at the same time, it seems to be a respectable introduction to MMORPGs for the n00bie. Thats fine. <br />
<br />
I see a lot of tradeskill props in here. None of you wore Tae Ew? Or Valorium Rings of Gallantry? Are you folks telling me there isnt ANY useless tradeskilling in WoW? Come on. <br />
<br />
<br />
And honestly, is "the abaility to solo with any class at any level" REALLY a plus? It may seem that way, but lets look back at the early days of EQ. Players in those days were seperated by one, basic thing. Time played. It took TIME to level. WoW doesnt seem to have that feature. In the end, this may be ok, but speaking as a veteran of EQ, I guarentee you if I coulda made lvl 50 in the first month of EQ, I probably wouldnt be playing. <br />
<br />
WoW has had to advantage of seeing all of EQs mistakes, and avoiding the same pit-falls. But we have to remember something. Ease of play, and ease of leveling, and the ability to do your thing non-stop without ever interacting with anotehr soul isnt EVERYONES cup of tea. And I can already smell MASSIVE problems with the whole PVP thing. Theres a reason that EQ has 95% "blue" servers, and 5% "red" you know. <br />
<br />
I am not trying to cut on WoW, honestly. I would probably enjoy it if I tried it. But for myself, I am still having a lot of fun in EQ. Gates drove me to the brink of /deltree, but OoW brought me back with triple the incentive and fun factor. No other expansion in the history of EQ drove me like OoW seems too, and that includes PoP, LDoN, Kunark and Velious. <br />
<br />
EQ made a lot of mistakes. No one is denying it. Its hardly a "perfect" game now. WoW is probably a lot slicker, more polished version of EQ, from a company who has a proven track record of great games, and the benefit of having a WHOLE LONG LIST of what NOT to do based on EQs mistakes. <br />
<br />
But they are diffferent games folks. You cant compare EQ now to WoW now. You cant compare EQ 5 years ago to WOW now. And you cant compare WoW in 5 years to EQ now. They are different, and if a new, exciting, dare I say "Magical" enduring world is what you are looking for, then WoW may be the best choice for you. Speaking for myself, Blazz is a part of my life. I will be hard pressed to hang up his Spellbook for ever. I, personally, just dont think WoW is the one that has "what it takes" for me. And lets face it, if EQ dies, and WoW turns out to be "The One", how hard will it be for a guy like me to buy it, load it, and catch up. Judging from the reports I see, it wont be too difficult at all.</p>
	
	
	
