<tr>
	<td class="alt2" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>Macheras</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Disciple<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Apr 2004<br />
	
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p><blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />Originally Posted by <b>Blazz</b><br /><i><br />
I see a lot of tradeskill props in here. None of you wore Tae Ew? Or Valorium Rings of Gallantry? Are you folks telling me there isnt ANY useless tradeskilling in WoW? Come on. <br />
</i><hr size="1" /></blockquote>There is no useless tradeskilling in WoW.  Period.<br />
<br />
Tae EW and Valorium needed relatively rare drops obtainable arguably 60ish level and those that could get and make them raped the rest of the world on prices.  (BTW, never bought or wore a single piece of Tae Ew :P).<br />
<br />
WoW tradeskills immediately provide a viable source of gear and other items almost immediately and progresses with you as you go.  There is no basis for comparison really, WoW wins hands down.<br />
<br />
Yes, the option of soloing to 60 in WoW is a good thing.  Period.  <br />
[EDIT: Key issue here is "option".  WoW has made it so soloing provides a viable means of character advancement in both levelling and loot.  Unlike EQ.  Do I intend to solo the whole time, no?  Again, it is a viable option.  If your friends aren't on you can still advance meaninfully.]<br />
<br />
And do we all think that as soon as you hit 60 it's game over, you won??  That is ludicrous and just because EQ had nothing to do or DAoC had nothing to do or Shadowbane had nothing to do or SWG had nothing to do at high levels at the start doesn't mean WoW will follow that same path.  Given how they've improved upon every annoying aspect of an MMORPG so far, I find it hard to believe that anyone can logically think they will screw up the high level game and allow for longevity and replayablitly. <br />
<br />
Mach</p>
	
	
	
